Attempting to provide canonical dotfiles, configuration, themes, etc across
various environments. Supported environments:
darwin / ns / mac
cygwin / win32
linux


* To install:
** Clone repo
** Setup submodules
$ cd <repo>
$ git submodule update --init
$ cd emacs.d/vendor/rinari # Gotta be a better way
$ git submodule update --init
** Create symlink in $HOME pointing to the repo
$ ln -s path/to/repo $HOME/.dotfiles
** Create symlinks for configs relative to the new symlink
$ ln -s $HOME/bashrc .bashrc

